{"THETA":[{"def":"A letter of the Greek alphabet corresponding to th in English; -- sometimes called the unlucky letter, from being used by the judges on their ballots in passing condemnation on a prisoner, it being the first letter of the Greek qa`natos, death.","pos":""}],"THETICAL":[{"def":"Laid down; absolute or positive, as a law.","pos":""}],"THETINE":[{"def":"Any one of a series of complex basic sulphur compounds analogous to the sulphines.","pos":""},{"def":"Of or pertaining to theurgy; magical.","pos":""}]}